WEBVTT

00:02.102 --> 00:03.569
I've got to admit, dad,
you really surprise me.

00:03.571 --> 00:06.238
Giving sam your old car
is really generous.

00:06.240 --> 00:08.073
You're getting soft
in your old age.

00:08.075 --> 00:10.476
Hey, she's my grandbaby.
I want her driving around
in something safe.

00:10.478 --> 00:11.777
So what are you gonna use
to get around?

00:11.779 --> 00:13.479
I'm gonna keep
driving my car.

00:13.481 --> 00:16.215
Excuse me?

00:16.217 --> 00:19.551
I figure you're only gonna
take sam out for a driving
lesson once a week.

00:19.553 --> 00:23.756
And you can call
and schedule the time
to use it whenever you want.

00:23.758 --> 00:27.259
Schedule a time?
Hold on.

00:27.261 --> 00:30.129
Who's gonna pay for
the maintenance and the tags
and everything else?

00:30.131 --> 00:31.797
Well, I'm old-fashioned,
and, you know,

00:31.799 --> 00:34.733
I'd make sam get a job
so she could pay for it,

00:34.735 --> 00:36.702
But it'll probably
end up being you.

00:38.438 --> 00:40.439
You're like
an evil tom sawyer.

00:40.441 --> 00:43.142
I'm not gonna paint
your fence

00:43.144 --> 00:45.110
And I'm not
gonna buy your car.
Here, take your pink slip back.

00:45.112 --> 00:47.446
It's too late.
I already told sam
and she's thrilled.

00:47.448 --> 00:50.049
But if you want to break
her heart, it's your car.

00:51.284 --> 00:52.785
You can't take advantage
of me, old man.

00:52.787 --> 00:56.088
I know where you live
because I pay your rent.

00:56.090 --> 00:58.157
This is why
you don't get cable.

01:02.262 --> 01:04.530
Sorry. Sorry.

01:04.532 --> 01:07.666
I'm sure you all heard that.
Little problem with my dad.

01:07.668 --> 01:09.468
I accidentally confused him

01:09.470 --> 01:12.271
With a caring
and loving grandfather.

01:12.273 --> 01:14.206
How'd that make you feel?

01:14.208 --> 01:16.742
Well, thanks, ed.
I appreciate your concern.

01:16.744 --> 01:18.277
It was a little upsetting.

01:18.279 --> 01:19.778
- Really?
- Yeah.

01:19.780 --> 01:22.247
Why don't we talk about it
for six months?

01:23.349 --> 01:25.451
Did you use your tools?

01:25.453 --> 01:28.253
Well, you're clearly having
a worse day than usual.

01:28.255 --> 01:30.789
Why, because
I'm not my usual

01:30.791 --> 01:33.826
Ray of goddamn sunshine?

01:33.828 --> 01:38.797
Talk about the positive
things we can take from
negative experiences.

01:38.799 --> 01:41.567
For example, I just found
another reason

01:41.569 --> 01:44.203
Not to be sad
when my dad dies.

01:45.105 --> 01:47.172
- Who wants to go next?
- I will.

01:47.174 --> 01:49.875
I had a negative experience
that taught me

01:49.877 --> 01:53.312
That a good friend is the most
important thing in the world.

01:53.314 --> 01:55.214
Well, that's great.
How did you learn that?

01:55.216 --> 01:57.616
'cause I was at this club
and this girl gave me
a dirty look.

01:57.618 --> 02:01.120
So I threw my drink
in her face, but the stir
stick hit her in the eye

02:01.122 --> 02:04.857
And her friend was nice enough
to take her to the hospital.

02:04.859 --> 02:07.226
That meant a lot to me.

02:07.228 --> 02:10.596
I've got another
positive spin on that story.

02:10.598 --> 02:15.434
Well, an innocent girl
got tired of using
her eyeball,

02:15.436 --> 02:18.904
So lacey tries
to poke it out for her.

02:18.906 --> 02:21.607
Of course,
I'm not a professional.

02:21.609 --> 02:24.376
I can tell you
what else you're not--
a subtle drunk.

02:24.378 --> 02:26.845
I can smell the old grand-dad
from here, old granddad.

02:28.181 --> 02:29.515
Ed, what's in the can?

02:29.517 --> 02:31.316
Narc.

02:31.318 --> 02:33.218
Ed, you can't drink
in group.

02:33.220 --> 02:35.888
I can fix that.
I'll go home.

02:35.890 --> 02:39.892
Hey, look,
I made a positive
out of a negative.

02:39.894 --> 02:41.927
Ed, ed, ed,
please sit down.

02:41.929 --> 02:43.695
No, no,
it won't do any good.

02:43.697 --> 02:46.798
I'm not getting any better.
What's 20 minutes gonna do?

02:46.800 --> 02:49.568
I'll just call my wife
and tell her to burn
my dinner early.

02:49.570 --> 02:51.537
She's the only reason
I'm here anyway.

02:51.539 --> 02:54.173
Wow. Your wife
makes you come here?

02:54.175 --> 02:56.308
No, it's purely
coincidental

02:56.310 --> 03:00.179
That if I don't come,
my wife said she'd leave me.

03:00.181 --> 03:03.715
Ed, ed, these are
all things you should
talk about in group.

03:03.717 --> 03:05.250
Why don't you
stick around?

03:05.252 --> 03:06.785
Nope, I'm leaving.
You can't stop me.

03:06.787 --> 03:09.188
Yeah, let's just leave that
to the telephone pole

03:09.190 --> 03:11.190
At the end of the block.

03:11.192 --> 03:14.226
Okay, because of that,
you're taking ed home.

03:14.228 --> 03:16.728
Hey, it's all right
with me.

03:16.730 --> 03:19.798
'cause I actually care
about my fellow human beings.

03:19.800 --> 03:22.634
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
That was way too easy.

03:22.636 --> 03:24.236
Where were you planning
on taking him?

03:24.238 --> 03:26.738
Transvestite bar
in koreatown.

03:28.675 --> 03:31.243
- Lacey, would you
take ed home?
- I'd be glad to.

03:31.245 --> 03:33.345
Whoa, whoa, whoa, lacey.

03:34.280 --> 03:36.915
Black comedy club,
south central.

03:36.917 --> 03:40.285
- Nolan?
- Yeah?

03:40.287 --> 03:42.454
I trust you.

03:42.456 --> 03:43.822
Would you please
take ed home?

03:43.824 --> 03:45.824
Okay.

03:45.826 --> 03:47.759
I only have a twin bed,

03:47.761 --> 03:49.494
But we can sleep
head to toe.

03:52.799 --> 03:54.566
Charlie:
<i>Ah, that was great.</i>

03:54.568 --> 03:56.668
I told you you'd like it.

03:56.670 --> 03:58.604
High five.

04:01.274 --> 04:04.843
Listen, I'm having a problem
with one of my patients.

04:04.845 --> 04:07.913
Seriously?
Untie me.

04:07.915 --> 04:09.448
Well, I would, but then
you wouldn't listen to me

04:09.450 --> 04:12.251
Talk about
one of my patients.

04:12.253 --> 04:14.653
Ed has been
very disruptive in group.

04:14.655 --> 04:16.822
- Pickles.
- What?

04:16.824 --> 04:18.991
- I thought that
was our safe word.
- No, we changed it.

04:18.993 --> 04:21.326
Anyway, he's a tough old guy.

04:21.328 --> 04:23.262
I've had clients that age.

04:23.264 --> 04:24.730
Sometimes they're just
too set in their ways.

04:24.732 --> 04:26.932
If he's a problem,
cut him loose.

04:26.934 --> 04:29.735
While you're at it,
cut me loose, too.

04:29.737 --> 04:31.837
No. No.
No man left behind.

04:31.839 --> 04:33.839
I've got to find
a way to help him.

04:33.841 --> 04:35.007
Spackle.

04:35.009 --> 04:37.309
Close.

04:37.311 --> 04:40.279
But it doesn't matter.
I thought maybe we could
go again.

04:40.281 --> 04:43.382
Yeah, I used that chinese
herb stuff you gave me

04:43.384 --> 04:45.817
For my birthday
and it works.

04:45.819 --> 04:48.954
No wonder they got
two billion people.

04:48.956 --> 04:52.291
You're kidding me.
I forgot to get you a gift,

04:52.293 --> 04:54.526
So I just dumped some spices
and tea in a jar.

04:54.528 --> 04:57.529
- That was a joke.
- So it was all me?

04:57.531 --> 05:00.432
Well, I'd like to think
I was in there somewhere.

05:00.434 --> 05:02.734
Maybe this could
work for ed?

05:02.736 --> 05:05.737
Are you two having
trouble in the bedroom?

05:05.739 --> 05:07.739
No, no, no.
But if I can convince ed

05:07.741 --> 05:10.075
To take some kind
of magic bullet that'll
suppress his anger,

05:10.077 --> 05:12.477
He'll believe it
and feel less angry.

05:12.479 --> 05:14.046
Nope, bad idea.

05:14.048 --> 05:16.982
Placebos are fine
for drug research,
but not for therapy.

05:16.984 --> 05:19.418
And are you okay
with lying to a patient?

05:19.420 --> 05:20.952
Well, I'll have
to tell him eventually,

05:20.954 --> 05:23.088
But hopefully by then
he'll have enough
positive results

05:23.090 --> 05:25.324
And realize that it was
in him all along.

05:25.326 --> 05:26.692
But you tell me
if you think I'm wrong.

05:26.694 --> 05:29.094
You're wrong.

05:29.096 --> 05:31.363
See?
Even you're not sure.

05:32.498 --> 05:34.933
<i>( theme music playing )</i>

05:37.503 --> 05:40.038
Holy crap.
How many pages
do I have to fill out

05:40.040 --> 05:42.441
Just so you can
go on a field trip
to feed the homeless?

05:42.443 --> 05:44.609
Well, I need your permission
to go into that neighborhood.

05:44.611 --> 05:46.445
There's a homeless
neighborhood?

05:46.447 --> 05:49.414
Here's an idea.
Let's build some houses there.

05:49.416 --> 05:51.650
Okay, fine.
Let's do this.

05:52.585 --> 05:54.553
"does your child have lice?"

05:54.555 --> 05:56.488
No.

05:56.490 --> 05:58.790
"any emotional issues
or disorders that might
create a difficulty

05:58.792 --> 06:00.792
For your child to participate
in this activity?"

06:01.861 --> 06:04.529
Do we finally tell them
I have ocd or not?

06:04.531 --> 06:06.431
I thought we were going
to save that little gem
for college

06:06.433 --> 06:08.066
When we start begging
for financial aid.

06:09.435 --> 06:11.470
You write down ocd,
sweetheart,

06:11.472 --> 06:13.872
And it could ruin your chances
of getting a job someday.

06:13.874 --> 06:15.540
Or it could help me land

06:15.542 --> 06:18.910
That touch-everything-twice job
I've always dreamt about.

06:18.912 --> 06:20.712
Thanks for the parenting
advice, dad,

06:20.714 --> 06:23.682
But we want sam
to think of you as more
of a cautionary tale.

06:25.118 --> 06:28.754
All right, we will leave
this decision for the next
field trip.

06:28.756 --> 06:30.589
- There you go, sweetie.
- Thank you.

06:30.591 --> 06:33.692
You ask me, all this
paperwork's a lot of nonsense.

06:33.694 --> 06:36.495
When I was a kid,
we learned how to milk
rattlesnakes in school

06:36.497 --> 06:39.131
And nobody
had to sign crap.

06:39.133 --> 06:42.501
Are you ever going to
stop being a pain in the ass
or have you just given up?

06:46.005 --> 06:49.508
Hey, charlie,
before I leave, can I ask
you something about kate?

06:49.510 --> 06:51.143
Does she hate me?

06:51.145 --> 06:53.612
No. No, she likes you.
Why?

06:53.614 --> 06:56.581
Well, I texted her
a couple of times about
us going out together

06:56.583 --> 06:58.650
And she never
got back to me.

06:58.652 --> 07:00.986
- I know she's really busy.
- Well, it kind of bums me out.

07:00.988 --> 07:02.788
I mean, I barely have
any women friends

07:02.790 --> 07:05.657
And I just thought, you know,
you guys are so close,

07:05.659 --> 07:07.592
She must be pretty fun
to hang out with.

07:07.594 --> 07:10.829
I wouldn't say fun.

07:10.831 --> 07:13.799
I mean, we're friends,
but I bring, like,

07:13.801 --> 07:16.501
80% of the fun.

07:16.503 --> 07:19.004
She may be 10.

07:19.006 --> 07:20.572
There's another 10%
that's, like,

07:20.574 --> 07:22.607
I don't know,
accidental fun.

07:22.609 --> 07:25.143
Well, then, maybe think
about the three of us

07:25.145 --> 07:27.846
Doing something
together sometime.
That could be fun.

07:27.848 --> 07:29.614
Oh, I have
thought about it.

07:29.616 --> 07:31.917
( chuckles )
you're right,
it could be fun.

07:33.586 --> 07:35.720
Hey, guys.
Thanks for coming in early.

07:35.722 --> 07:37.222
Something I want
to talk to you about.

07:37.224 --> 07:38.557
Hey, where's ed?

07:38.559 --> 07:40.158
That's what this is about.

07:40.160 --> 07:42.060
I asked him to come
at the normal time.

07:42.062 --> 07:45.697
Now, I know we all think
ed can be a pain at times,

07:45.699 --> 07:47.699
But deep down I think
we all care about him

07:47.701 --> 07:49.000
And don't want to see
him suffer, right?

07:49.002 --> 07:51.570
Oh, my god.
We're gonna have
him put down.

07:51.572 --> 07:54.673
No, we're not gonna
have ed destroyed.

07:54.675 --> 07:57.609
- But...
-  <i>No.</i>

07:57.611 --> 07:59.811
I'm just gonna be trying
a new technique on him.

07:59.813 --> 08:03.048
But in order for it to work,
I need you all to participate.

08:03.050 --> 08:05.517
You're gonna be taking
placebo pills.

08:05.519 --> 08:07.519
<i>I'm gonna tell ed</i>
<i>that it's been proven</i>

08:07.521 --> 08:09.254
To decrease anger
and negativity

08:09.256 --> 08:12.591
While filling you with
a sense of euphoria and love
for your fellow man.

08:12.593 --> 08:14.559
- Like ecstasy.
- Yeah, yeah.

08:14.561 --> 08:16.761
I guess we're pretending
that there are similar
qualities, sure.

08:16.763 --> 08:19.231
Well, why can't you
just give us ecstasy?

08:19.233 --> 08:20.699
Because it's illegal

08:20.701 --> 08:22.734
And I'm not gonna
hand out any real drugs.

08:22.736 --> 08:25.270
That you've been taking it
for a week and it works.

08:25.272 --> 08:26.972
I have a better idea.

08:26.974 --> 08:28.974
Why don't you give ed
the sugar pill

08:28.976 --> 08:32.244
And we'll take
the ecstasy?

08:32.246 --> 08:35.180
( sighs )
I'm not giving
anybody ecstasy.

08:35.182 --> 08:36.748
<i>You're all taking</i>
<i>sugar pills.</i>

08:36.750 --> 08:38.650
It's called
deception therapy.

08:38.652 --> 08:40.886
But the only way it works
is if you all participate.

08:40.888 --> 08:43.188
One more question.

08:43.190 --> 08:47.592
Will this placebo
react badly with my ecstasy?

08:49.295 --> 08:52.831
Ed.
Perfect timing.

08:52.833 --> 08:54.633
I was just checking
the results of the new pills

08:54.635 --> 08:56.668
I gave the group after
you left early last week.

08:56.670 --> 08:57.903
What kind of pills?

08:57.905 --> 09:00.872
It's a pill that actually
reduces anger

09:00.874 --> 09:03.108
While promoting feelings
of love and tolerance.

09:03.110 --> 09:04.976
I'd love for you to be
part of the test group.

09:04.978 --> 09:07.312
We're seeing great results.
Just ask patrick.

09:09.181 --> 09:11.950
Well, uh,
I started a week ago

09:11.952 --> 09:15.086
And I have
never felt happier.

09:15.088 --> 09:16.821
Which kind of happy?

09:16.823 --> 09:18.823
I just got
cher tickets happy

09:18.825 --> 09:22.193
Or I just met the queer guy
from "glee" happy?

09:22.195 --> 09:23.862
( laughs )

09:23.864 --> 09:26.631
Oh, edward.

09:26.633 --> 09:28.767
You see?
Patrick's a totally
different person.

09:28.769 --> 09:31.770
But this one's gay, too.

09:31.772 --> 09:34.105
All right,
maybe I will try

09:34.107 --> 09:36.841
As long as it
doesn't interfere with
my cholesterol medicine.

09:36.843 --> 09:39.010
- It won't.
- What about my blood
pressure pills?

09:39.012 --> 09:41.746
- Absolutely not.
- My prostate pills?

09:41.748 --> 09:44.149
Antifungal?
Blood thinner?

09:44.151 --> 09:46.685
Restless leg?
Sleepy leg?

09:46.687 --> 09:49.921
No, I'm pretty sure
this is one that just
blends in with the crowd.

09:49.923 --> 09:52.591
All right.
You've sold me on it.

09:52.593 --> 09:54.693
I'll go get some water.

09:54.695 --> 09:58.597
Because if it doesn't,
I'll probably lose my wife,

09:58.599 --> 10:01.333
My house, and everything
that's dear to me.

10:01.335 --> 10:04.836
Mmm, sugary.

10:08.107 --> 10:11.242
I just got your text.

10:11.244 --> 10:13.945
Please don't make me
go out with jen.

10:13.947 --> 10:16.047
Just once.

10:16.049 --> 10:19.250
Otherwise she wants
to hang out with both of us
on our playdate nights.

10:19.252 --> 10:21.186
And that's worse.
Right?

10:22.121 --> 10:24.122
Right.

10:24.124 --> 10:25.690
I can't do it.

10:25.692 --> 10:27.192
I hate lying to jen
about us.

10:27.194 --> 10:29.260
It makes me feel
like a creep.

10:29.262 --> 10:31.262
Look, you and I were
just friends back when jen
and I were still married.

10:31.264 --> 10:33.231
If she finds out
we're sleeping
together now,

10:33.233 --> 10:35.200
She'll never believe
we weren't doing it
back then.

10:35.202 --> 10:39.104
Even if that's true,
jen and I have nothing
in common.

10:39.106 --> 10:41.873
It'll be way better than
her trying to hang out

10:41.875 --> 10:43.708
With us on the nights
we want to have sex.

10:43.710 --> 10:46.144
Right?

10:46.146 --> 10:47.946
Let me know.

10:51.150 --> 10:52.651
All right.

10:52.653 --> 10:54.185
How are those pills
working out for everybody?

10:54.187 --> 10:55.387
- Awesome.
- Great.

10:56.355 --> 10:57.922
Ed?

11:00.292 --> 11:03.228
I'm so happy
I could kiss all of you.

11:04.363 --> 11:06.264
Ed, what's happening
to your face?

11:06.266 --> 11:08.266
Are you having
some kind of a stroke?

11:08.268 --> 11:10.368
Oh, my god.
You're smiling.

11:10.370 --> 11:13.405
Yeah.
I've never been so happy.

11:13.407 --> 11:16.207
I was pulling out of
the home depot last night

11:16.209 --> 11:18.276
And somebody blocked me in.

11:18.278 --> 11:19.911
But I didn't get
pissed off.

11:19.913 --> 11:23.114
I just sat in my car
and watched two mexicans

11:23.116 --> 11:24.683
Eat shaved ice.

11:25.951 --> 11:27.252
It was beautiful.

11:27.254 --> 11:31.322
Actually, ed,
I think any ethnicity

11:31.324 --> 11:33.358
Eating shaved ice
is beautiful.

11:33.360 --> 11:35.860
That is a good thought,
patrick.

11:39.198 --> 11:41.800
Oh, before we start,
my wife and I

11:41.802 --> 11:45.203
Are having a little shindig
for our 40th this weekend

11:45.205 --> 11:47.305
And she asked me
to invite my friends.

11:47.307 --> 11:49.908
I look around this room

11:49.910 --> 11:52.177
And that's all I see.

11:52.179 --> 11:53.845
I'd be honored to come.

11:53.847 --> 11:56.247
And I'm sure everybody else
would be as well.

11:56.249 --> 11:57.882
- No, I can't.
- I have plans.

11:57.884 --> 12:00.385
I'm bleeding.

12:00.387 --> 12:02.320
That's too bad.

12:02.322 --> 12:04.456
You remember
that brother-in-law
I told you about?

12:04.458 --> 12:06.758
The one I went after
with a machete

12:06.760 --> 12:09.127
In that game of horseshoes
a couple of years ago.

12:09.129 --> 12:13.031
Well, I feel so good
that I've invited him

12:13.033 --> 12:15.100
And we're gonna finish
that game of horseshoes.

12:15.102 --> 12:17.736
- Yeah, I could make that.
- I would like to come.

12:17.738 --> 12:20.105
- That's fine.
- Ed, ed, this is amazing.

12:20.107 --> 12:23.308
He triggered probably
your worst blackout rage.

12:23.310 --> 12:24.843
I'll tell you, charlie,
he makes me mad.

12:24.845 --> 12:27.946
Well, used to.
But I feel like a new man now.

12:27.948 --> 12:29.948
And I'd just like to say
thank you.

12:29.950 --> 12:32.283
- You're welcome, ed.
- Not to you.

12:32.285 --> 12:34.352
To the guy that invented
those pills.

12:34.354 --> 12:37.055
Now if the pill can only
do something

12:37.057 --> 12:38.423
About my damn prostate.

12:40.960 --> 12:43.361
This is fantastic.

12:43.363 --> 12:47.098
Ed is on the verge
of a tremendous
breakthrough.

12:47.100 --> 12:49.901
We are about to witness
the power of the human mind

12:49.903 --> 12:52.403
Overcoming years
of hostility and anger.

12:52.405 --> 12:54.439
Yeah, and we're probably
gonna get to watch him

12:54.441 --> 12:56.841
Kill his brother-in-law
with a horseshoe.

12:59.512 --> 13:01.546
And that's why
I'm convinced

13:01.548 --> 13:05.350
That my little hungarian
grandmother on the way
to ellis island

13:05.352 --> 13:07.118
Invented the body shot.

