14:16.857 --> 14:19.457
Listen, you're looking
for a guy, I'm looking
for a guy.

14:19.459 --> 14:21.492
We could go
hunting together.

14:21.494 --> 14:23.328
( gasps )
we're cougars.

14:25.097 --> 14:26.397
You don't want
to hang out with me.

14:26.399 --> 14:28.266
I'm an academic.
I'm really not
a lot of fun.

14:28.268 --> 14:31.502
- That's what charlie said.
- Really?

14:31.504 --> 14:34.272
Yeah, but, you know, I bet
under all that black stuff

14:34.274 --> 14:37.275
Is somebody who wants to
bust out and have a good time.

14:37.277 --> 14:38.409
Here's the deal.

14:38.411 --> 14:41.179
Thursday, el tostada
on ventura boulevard,

14:41.181 --> 14:43.181
Half-price
skinny margaritas.

14:43.183 --> 14:46.351
You like musicians?
Because there's a guitar
store down the block

14:46.353 --> 14:48.319
And a bunch of those dudes
come in.

14:48.321 --> 14:51.022
Oh, that is definitely
something

14:51.024 --> 14:53.291
I would only do
with you.

14:53.293 --> 14:55.660
Then, to us.

14:55.662 --> 14:57.262
Meow!

14:57.264 --> 14:59.163
( laughs )

14:59.165 --> 15:01.065
Yeah, don't do that.

15:02.468 --> 15:05.236
<i>( music playing )</i>

15:07.072 --> 15:09.374
Hey, guys.
Sorry I'm late.

15:09.376 --> 15:11.142
- Hell of a time
finding this place.
- Me, too.

15:11.144 --> 15:13.177
I put "white racist guy"
in my gps,

15:13.179 --> 15:15.179
This whole side
of town lit up.

15:15.181 --> 15:19.017
I know.
Pretty sure I drove past
a white angus steakhouse.

15:19.019 --> 15:21.219
Lacey and I
just got here, too.

15:21.221 --> 15:23.488
We had to stop and buy
some vitamins from her friend

15:23.490 --> 15:25.123
In a burger king
parking lot.

15:25.125 --> 15:26.925
That's worrisome.

15:26.927 --> 15:30.361
Hey, there's ed.
We should go over
and give him a hug.

15:30.363 --> 15:33.498
Wait, we should give
each other a hug.

15:33.500 --> 15:35.667
Are you drunk?

15:35.669 --> 15:37.435
No, I'm just on ecstasy.

15:37.437 --> 15:40.672
But I did wash it down
with a mojito.

15:42.207 --> 15:43.508
We'll talk about
this in group.

15:43.510 --> 15:45.410
Yes, we will
and for the rest
of our lives.

15:45.412 --> 15:48.546
I'm dancing away.

15:48.548 --> 15:52.050
Hey, charlie.
Glad you could make it.

15:52.052 --> 15:53.985
Are you kidding?
I wouldn't have missed it.

15:53.987 --> 15:55.420
- How's everything going?
- Oh, pretty good.

15:55.422 --> 15:57.989
Wife's happy.
Come here.

15:57.991 --> 16:00.625
I need to ask you
a question.

16:00.627 --> 16:04.062
Is it safe to take
two of these in one day?

16:04.064 --> 16:06.230
Sure.
It says as needed.

16:07.599 --> 16:10.134
Good, because here comes
that son of a bitch again.

16:10.136 --> 16:14.706
Come on, tell me where
you're hiding the good
scotch, you cheap bastard.

16:14.708 --> 16:16.307
Hi there.
I'm charlie.

16:16.309 --> 16:18.376
You must be ray,
ed's brother-in-law.

16:18.378 --> 16:21.112
That's who I am.
Thanks, I almost forgot.

16:21.114 --> 16:22.413
Jerkoff.

16:24.316 --> 16:27.251
No, seriously.
It's good to meet you.

16:27.253 --> 16:30.521
Ray, these are
friends of mine.
This is a party.

16:30.523 --> 16:33.491
I'd appreciate it if you'd
make a little effort.

16:33.493 --> 16:38.029
And who among us wouldn't
be better off by making
a little effort?

16:38.031 --> 16:40.164
Wait a minute.
I know who you are.
You're ed's shrink.

16:40.166 --> 16:42.266
- That's right.
- Well, congratulations.

16:42.268 --> 16:45.169
You turned him
into a real puss.

16:45.171 --> 16:47.171
I tried to take him
on a hunting trip.

16:47.173 --> 16:49.173
He said, "no.
Too many anger triggers."

16:49.175 --> 16:51.009
Puss!

16:51.011 --> 16:53.311
Ed, weren't you gonna
show me around the house?

16:53.313 --> 16:55.046
No.

16:55.048 --> 16:58.049
Yeah, give him a tour
of casa disappointment.

16:58.051 --> 17:01.219
And after that,
I want to finish
that game of horseshoes.

17:01.221 --> 17:03.254
I've been waiting a long time
to kick your butt.

17:03.256 --> 17:05.289
You got it, ray.

17:05.291 --> 17:07.625
Ed, ed, ed.
Can I talk to you
for a second?

17:10.129 --> 17:12.130
Ed.

17:12.132 --> 17:14.098
Look, you've been
doing a great job.

17:14.100 --> 17:16.200
But now it's time to walk
away from this guy.

17:16.202 --> 17:18.770
I can handle this.
I just need to take
a few more of these pills.

17:18.772 --> 17:22.507
Look, ray is beyond
what these can handle.

17:23.776 --> 17:26.144
Truth is they're--
they're sugar pills, ed.

17:26.146 --> 17:28.146
They're placebos.

17:28.148 --> 17:30.114
You've been giving me
sugar pills?

17:30.116 --> 17:31.682
Well, here's the best part.

17:31.684 --> 17:34.285
That means you've been
controlling your anger
on your own.

17:34.287 --> 17:37.522
You used to be ed
the angry old guy.

17:37.524 --> 17:40.591
Now you're ed
the old guy.

17:42.127 --> 17:45.430
And everybody knew
about this but me?

17:45.432 --> 17:48.332
I feel like
a damn fool.

17:48.334 --> 17:51.702
You've got about 10 seconds
to get off my property.

17:51.704 --> 17:54.072
Ed.

17:54.074 --> 17:57.075
Ed, ed, you're not a fool.

17:57.077 --> 17:59.510
You've had a breakthrough.
So why don't we just
enjoy the party

17:59.512 --> 18:01.179
And we'll talk about this
Tuesday in group?

18:01.181 --> 18:02.713
What do I need group for?

18:02.715 --> 18:07.085
You just said that
I can control my own
anger on my own.

18:07.087 --> 18:11.122
I'm changing my mind.
Pack up the guns and booze.

18:11.124 --> 18:12.423
We're going hunting.

18:12.425 --> 18:14.292
All right.

18:18.430 --> 18:19.697
So it didn't go well?

18:19.699 --> 18:21.833
Hey, for a placebo test,
it went very well.

18:21.835 --> 18:24.535
Usually half the group gets
heart disease or cancer.

18:24.537 --> 18:26.304
Ed didn't get any of that.

18:26.306 --> 18:28.606
But you lost a patient
because you tricked him.

18:28.608 --> 18:30.775
I know, I know.
He doesn't trust me anymore.
I get it.

18:30.777 --> 18:33.611
So why do you think you went
so far to help this guy?

18:33.613 --> 18:36.347
Good question.

18:39.818 --> 18:42.386
Well, does he remind
you of anyone?

18:42.388 --> 18:45.289
I don't know.
Just another old guy
like my dad.

18:45.291 --> 18:47.291
Real stubborn.

18:47.293 --> 18:49.393
Won't listen to anyone
like my dad.

18:49.395 --> 18:50.862
<i>Drinks a little.</i>

18:50.864 --> 18:54.732
Doesn't respect me,
you know, like my dad.

18:54.734 --> 18:56.834
You know who
he reminds me of?

18:56.836 --> 18:59.837
- Wilford brimley.
- Stop it.

18:59.839 --> 19:02.840
You know, ever since
your father came back
into your life,

19:02.842 --> 19:05.810
You've been extremely
frustrated with him.

19:05.812 --> 19:07.912
And you've transferred
your need to change your dad

19:07.914 --> 19:10.414
Into another
stubborn old guy-- ed.

19:10.416 --> 19:12.617
You're not going
to change ed,

19:12.619 --> 19:15.186
So break this pattern.
Let him go.

19:15.188 --> 19:16.854
You're right.

19:16.856 --> 19:18.422
I'm gonna go get ed back.

19:20.492 --> 19:22.460
<i>( knocking )</i>

19:24.229 --> 19:25.730
What do you want?

19:25.732 --> 19:28.533
I want to apologize.

19:31.203 --> 19:34.305
One of my jobs
as your therapist is
to help build your trust.

19:34.307 --> 19:36.607
And in this case,
I feel like I might have

19:36.609 --> 19:38.609
Taken advantage of it.

19:38.611 --> 19:41.212
So you want me
to come back, I guess.

19:41.214 --> 19:42.813
Yes, I do.

19:42.815 --> 19:48.452
Just the chance to
make your life free from
the emotional turmoil

19:48.454 --> 19:51.255
That's followed you
around like a black dog
for the last 70 years.

19:51.257 --> 19:53.891
Not enough.

19:53.893 --> 19:55.927
I want a discount.

19:55.929 --> 19:57.728
20%.

19:57.730 --> 19:59.330
This set me way back.

19:59.332 --> 20:01.666
You're right,
it was a horrible setback

20:01.668 --> 20:04.202
And I am responsible.

20:04.204 --> 20:07.638
But I'm seeing this
as more of a 10% setback.

20:07.640 --> 20:09.840
10's fair.

20:09.842 --> 20:11.943
I'll just grab my sweater.

20:11.945 --> 20:14.645
Oh, and I need
your sigmund freud
on that.

20:15.914 --> 20:18.316
Ed, this is from
the superior court
of los angeles.

20:18.318 --> 20:20.918
Yeah, I forgot to tell you.

20:20.920 --> 20:24.422
They said if I don't want
to go to jail, I've got to go
back to anger management.

20:24.424 --> 20:27.959
You tried to kill
your brother-in-law?

20:27.961 --> 20:31.429
No. I just took him
deer hunting.

20:31.431 --> 20:32.863
We got in the middle
of the woods

20:32.865 --> 20:35.833
And I made him put
some antlers on his head

20:35.835 --> 20:40.304
And run through the forest
making deer noises.

20:40.306 --> 20:42.540
Okay. Wow.

20:42.542 --> 20:45.009
Many questions.

20:45.011 --> 20:47.845
Why would he agree
to that?

20:47.847 --> 20:49.647
A man will agree
to a lot

20:49.649 --> 20:52.450
If a gun's pointed
at his nuts.

20:52.452 --> 20:55.419
So legally you had
to come back anyway.

20:55.421 --> 20:58.422
Yep.
Tricked you.

20:58.424 --> 21:00.625
Feels good, don't it?

21:02.394 --> 21:04.929
Oh, ed,
just one more thing.

21:04.931 --> 21:07.865
You said you made your
brother-in-law run around
and make deer noises.

21:07.867 --> 21:10.935
Just exactly what does
a deer sound like?

21:10.937 --> 21:13.971
Well, in this case,
it was, "help me! Help me!

21:13.973 --> 21:15.940
I'm a man, not a deer!"

21:17.576 --> 21:20.344
Thanks.
That was bugging me.
